thread.title: German tourists rescued in Georgia

author: eTN Global Editor
title: German tourists rescued in Georgia
text:
German tourists rescued in Georgia   
Sep 20, 2015 eTN   
TBILISI, Georgia - Georgian rescuers have helped a group of tourists from Germany in the area of ​​ Mount Ushba, where one of them was injured. 
The foreigners called the 112 center and reported that one of them couldn't move independently due to serious foot injuries. 
Seven rescuers and a duty detail of border guards helped the tourist to get to the village of Becho, located at a distance of 10 km from where the tourist was located, after which the injured tourist was taken to the hospital in Mestia, Georgia Online reports.
